explanation: This solution uses a doubly linked list to store the cache. The get operation traverses the list to find the key, removes it, and then adds it to the end to mark it as recently used. The put operation also traverses the list to find the key, removes it if it exists, and then adds it to the end. If the cache is full, it removes the front element. This solution has a time complexity of O(1) and a space complexity of O(capacity).

